Here is an implementation of the Longest Common Subsequence (LCS) algorithm using dynamic programming in Python:

```python
def lcs(s1, s2):
    m, n = len(s1), len(s2)
    dp = [[0 for _ in range(n + 1)] for _ in range(m + 1)]
    for i in range(1, m + 1):
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            if s1[i - 1] == s2[j - 1]:
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1
            else:
                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1])
    return dp[m][n]
```

